casebody.data:
No. 941,

Misc.

Saldana v. United States. Stephen R. Reinhardt for petitioner. Solicitor General Rankin, Assistant Attorney General Wilkey, Beatrice Rosenberg and Theodore George Gilin-sky for the United States. John T. McTeman, A. L. Wirin and Fred Okrand filed a brief for the American Civil Liberties Union of Southern California, as amicus curiae, in support of the petition.

Motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit granted. Case transferred to the appellate docket.
